#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_scale_bar.rst:71
msgid ""
"Select the units you want to use with :guilabel:`Scalebar units`. There "
"are many possible choices: **Map Units** (the default one), **Meters**, "
"**Feet**, **Miles** or **Nautical Miles**... which may force unit "
"conversions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_scale_bar.rst:74
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Label unit multiplier` specifies how many scale bar units "
"per labeled unit. Eg, if your scale bar units are set to \"meters\", a "
"multiplier of 1000 will result in the scale bar labels in \"kilometers\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_scale_bar.rst:77
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Label for units` field defines the text used to describe "
"the units of the scale bar, eg ``m`` or ``km``. This should be matched to"
" reflect the multiplier above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_scale_bar.rst:80
msgid ""
"You can define how many :guilabel:`Segments` will be drawn on the left "
"and on the right side of the scale bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_scale_bar.rst:82
msgid ""
"You can set how long each segment will be (:guilabel:`Fixed width`), or "
"limit the scale bar size in ``mm`` with :guilabel:`Fit segment width` "
"option. In the latter case, each time the map scale changes, the scale "
"bar is resized (and its label updated) to fit the range set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/print_composer/composer_items/composer_scale_bar.rst:86
